## 'telex-workflow.json'

Save this file in your project root as `telex-workflow.json`.

This is a Telex.im workflow definition that connects directly to your deployed agent endpoint.  
When you deploy your Mastra server (e.g. on Render, Railway, or Vercel), replace the placeholder URL.

```json
{
  "active": true,
  "category": "utilities",
  "description": "Fetches and summarizes historical events for today or any requested date",
  "id": "today_in_history_workflow",
  "long_description": "The Today in History Agent provides notable events from Wikipedia. Ask 'today' for today's events or 'history <month> <day>' for a specific date (e.g., 'history 7 4' for July 4th). Uses Wikipedia's 'On This Day' API and Google Gemini for intelligent responses.",
  "name": "Today in History Agent",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "today_history_node",
      "name": "Today in History",
      "parameters": {},
      "position": [100, 100],
      "type": "a2a/mastra-a2a-node",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "url": "https://today-in-history-agent-production.up.railway.app/a2a/message"
    }
  ],
  "settings": {
    "executionOrder": "v1"
  },
  "short_description": "Historical events for any date"
}
